 They candidly discuss the problems they have faced in writing and the strategies that enabled them to reach their goals. While obviously of interest to readers of Latin American literature, this book has important insights for students of women's literature and cultural studies, as well as for aspiring writers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aAuthors, Spanish American - 20th century - Interviews. 0aAuthors, Spanish Americany20th centuryvInterviews. 0aSpanish American literaturexWomen authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aSpanish American literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aWomen and literaturezLatin America. 0aWomen authors, Spanish Americany20th centuryvInterviews. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Caribbean & Latin American.2bisacsh1 aBalch, Trudy.1 aLears, Karen Parker.40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/73862140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292755918423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292755918/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK